ct. In The Life Intense, the first part of his ambitious Letting Be trilogy, he begins to develop it in detail. This first book focuses on ethics; the forthcoming two books look at politics and metaphysics respectively."  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mrz 2022) 0aConduct of life. 0aEthics. 0aLife. 4aPhilosophy. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Ethics & Moral Philosophy.2bisacsh1 aRayAlexander, Abigail, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aRayAlexander, Christopher, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEdinburgh University Press Complete eBook-Package 2018z978311078043740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781474437134423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781474437134/original  a978-3-11-078043-7  Edinburgh University Press Complete eBook-Package 2018b2018  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK